[
    {
        "content": "<p>Is there a reason why <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=abs_mul#doc\">docs#abs_mul</a> isn't tagged as <code>simp</code>?</p>",
        "id": 533639631,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1754819199
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>maybe you don't always want to <code>simp</code> it?</p>",
        "id": 533639719,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1754819306
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Well, what kind of circumstances lead to that?</p>",
        "id": 533639738,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1754819328
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I feel like <code>f (g a b) = g (h a) (h b)</code> is the quintessential form of a simp lemma, think e.g. <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Nat.cast_add#doc\">docs#Nat.cast_add</a> or <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Nat.cast_mul#doc\">docs#Nat.cast_mul</a></p>",
        "id": 533639840,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1754819419
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So I don't get why we're excluding this one</p>",
        "id": 533639851,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1754819434
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It may also be oversight, not sure</p>",
        "id": 533639967,
        "sender_full_name": "Ruben Van de Velde",
        "timestamp": 1754819535
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'll add the attribute and see if anything breaks</p>",
        "id": 533639984,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1754819549
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Worth a try</p>",
        "id": 533639993,
        "sender_full_name": "Ruben Van de Velde",
        "timestamp": 1754819560
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"459227\">Violeta Hernández</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/abs_mul.20simp/near/533639840\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I feel like <code>f (g a b) = g (h a) (h b)</code> is the quintessential form of a simp lemma, think e.g. <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Nat.cast_add#doc\">docs#Nat.cast_add</a> or <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Nat.cast_mul#doc\">docs#Nat.cast_mul</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>i'm talking about abs in particular</p>",
        "id": 533639996,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1754819563
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I can't recall an example</p>",
        "id": 533640024,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1754819591
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Well yeah, my point is I don't see anything specific about <code>abs</code> that'd make this attribute undesirable</p>",
        "id": 533640027,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1754819595
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Do we have <code>|a * a| = a * a</code> as simp?</p>",
        "id": 533640028,
        "sender_full_name": "Ruben Van de Velde",
        "timestamp": 1754819597
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=abs_sq#doc\">docs#abs_sq</a></p>",
        "id": 533640042,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1754819615
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Or <code>|a| * |a| = a * a</code></p>",
        "id": 533640045,
        "sender_full_name": "Ruben Van de Velde",
        "timestamp": 1754819618
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We don't, huh</p>",
        "id": 533640047,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1754819618
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh nvm, <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=abs_mul_abs_self#doc\">docs#abs_mul_abs_self</a> and <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=abs_mul_self#doc\">docs#abs_mul_self</a> are both <code>simp</code></p>",
        "id": 533640068,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1754819644
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think for <code>abs_sq</code> the reason is that <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=abs_pow#doc\">docs#abs_pow</a> would conflict with it</p>",
        "id": 533640133,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1754819725
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(on that note, it's odd we have both <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=abs_pow#doc\">docs#abs_pow</a> and <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=pow_abs#doc\">docs#pow_abs</a>)</p>",
        "id": 533640186,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1754819773
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/28176\">#28176</a> <span aria-label=\"fingers crossed\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f91e\" role=\"img\" title=\"fingers crossed\">:fingers_crossed:</span></p>",
        "id": 533640475,
